-- Homeowner Q2 vacancy rate 2.8 percent vs Q1 2.9 percent
-- 
-- Thu Jul 24, 2008 10:30am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/24/us-usa-housing-vacancies-idUSWBT00945820080724

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The share of homes owned but sitting empty inched down to 2.8 percent during the second quarter from 2.9 percent in the first quarter, the Census Bureau said on Thursday. 

 The homeownership rate was little changed, edging up to a seasonally adjusted 68.1 percent from 68.0 percent. (Editing by  James Dalgleish )